The '''Eurotransplant International Foundation''', commonly known simply as '''Eurotransplant''', is an international [[non-profit organization]] responsible for encouraging and coordinating [[organ transplant]]s in [[Austria]], [[Belgium]], [[Croatia]], [[Germany]], [[Hungary]], [[Luxembourg]], [[Netherlands]], and [[Slovenia]].<ref name="history">[http://www.eurotransplant.org/cms/index.php?page=history History], Eurotransplant. Retrieved on 17 October 2014.</ref> The organization was created by [[Jon J. van Rood]] in 1967 and legally founded on 12 May 1969.<ref name="history"/><ref>[https://www.eurotransplant.org/cms/mediaobject.php?file=ar_19951.pdf Annual Report 1995], Eurotransplant. Retrieved on 17 October 2014.</ref> The headquarters are located in [[Leiden]], Netherlands.<ref>[http://www.eurotransplant.org/cms/index.php?page=contact Contact], Eurotransplant. Retrieved on 17 October 2014.</ref>

All transplant clinics, [[tissue-typing laboratory|tissue-typing laboratories]], and hospitals in the member countries where [[organ donation]]s take place are included in the exchange. Eurotransplant helps coordinate work in these institutions, with the goal of efficiently allocating and distributing donated organs. The group also promotes research into transplantation and seeks to raise public awareness of the benefits of donation.{{cn|date=October 2014}}

Comparable institutions are [[Scandiatransplant]] in Iceland, Norway, Finland, Denmark, and Sweden; as well as [[Balttransplant]] in Estonia, Latvia, and Lithuania.

